chapter.verse:


a time to be born, and a time to 


die;




a time to plant, and a time to pluck up what is planted;



a time to 


weep, and a time to laugh;




a time to mourn, and a time to 


dance;



a time to 


cast away stones, and a time to 


gather stones together;




a time to embrace, and a time to 


refrain from embracing;



a time to seek, and a time to 


lose;




a time to keep, and a time to 


cast away;



a time to 


tear, and a time to sew;




a time to 


keep silence, and a time to speak;



a time to love, and a time to 


hate;




a time for war, and a time for peace.

I perceived that there is 


nothing better for them than to be joyful and to 


do good as long as they live;
